# Post-Build Input Copy

After building the QuickTag executable, copy staged test images from `.tmp/input` into the dist bundle's `input/` folder — but only when `.tmp/input` exists and contains at least one file.

| Platform | Dist input directory |
|----------|----------------------|
| Linux    | `dist/linux/quicktag/input` |
| Windows  | `dist/win/quicktag/input` |

`.tmp/` is gitignored; use it to stage local images for smoke-testing the built executable.

## build.sh (after PyInstaller and dist setup)

```bash
TMP_INPUT=".tmp/input"
if [[ -d "$TMP_INPUT" ]] && [[ -n "$(ls -A "$TMP_INPUT" 2>/dev/null)" ]]; then
    echo "==> Copying staged input images from $TMP_INPUT"
    cp -r "$TMP_INPUT"/. "$DIST_DIR/input/"
fi
```

## build.ps1 (after PyInstaller and dist setup)

```powershell
$TmpInput = Join-Path $ProjectRoot ".tmp\input"
if ((Test-Path $TmpInput) -and (Get-ChildItem -Path $TmpInput -Force | Select-Object -First 1)) {
    Write-Host "==> Copying staged input images from $TmpInput"
    Copy-Item -Path (Join-Path $TmpInput "*") -Destination (Join-Path $DistDir "input") -Recurse -Force
}
```

## When running builds manually

If you run `./build.sh` or `.\build.ps1` without modifying the scripts, perform the same copy step yourself when `.tmp/input` is populated.
